## Refactor Phase Complete

**Naming Evaluation**: All existing function names clearly reveal their intent. The new helpers `partitionByComponent` and `mainItemsBaseTotal` are descriptive and parallel to existing names like `componentsBaseTotal`.

**Refactoring Applied**: Extracted `partitionByComponent` helper and `mainItemsBaseTotal` helper, eliminating duplicate iteration over `items` in `policyBase`.

**Before**:
```typescript
const policyBase = (items: Item[]): number => {
  const mainBase = items.filter((i) => !isComponent(i)).reduce((sum, i) => sum + itemBasePremium(i), 0);
  const compBase = componentsBaseTotal(items.filter(isComponent));
  return mainBase + compBase;
};
```
- Iterates `items` THREE times (two filters + one reduce on filtered result)
- Inline reduce mixed with filter chain

**After**:
```typescript
const partitionByComponent = (items: Item[]): { mainItems: Item[]; components: Item[] } =>
  items.reduce<{ mainItems: Item[]; components: Item[] }>(
    (acc, item) => {
      (isComponent(item) ? acc.components : acc.mainItems).push(item);
      return acc;
    },
    { mainItems: [], components: [] },
  );

const mainItemsBaseTotal = (items: Item[]): number =>
  items.reduce((sum, item) => sum + itemBasePremium(item), 0);

const policyBase = (items: Item[]): number => {
  const { mainItems, components } = partitionByComponent(items);
  return mainItemsBaseTotal(mainItems) + componentsBaseTotal(components);
};
```
- `policyBase` now reads as a clear pipeline: partition, then sum each group
- `mainItemsBaseTotal` parallels existing `componentsBaseTotal` naming
- Single partition pass instead of two filter passes

**APP Mass Analysis**:

Before `policyBase` alone (excluding helpers): ~43 mass units (mix of two loops via filter + one reduce, multiple invocations, repeat scan of items)

After `policyBase` (3 lines): far simpler — destructure (2 bindings), 2 invocations + 1 invocation summing = ~11 mass. The extracted helpers each have well-bounded responsibilities. Net code is restructured into smaller composable units with one fewer pass over `items`.

**Tests**: All 21 passing tests remain green.

